There are twenty-seven translations, seven of which are from the Original Text. The Annus Sanctus contains three trans· lations. This beautiful hymn breathes the spirit of Ad- vent: it is an excellent summary of the Epistle (Rom. 13, 11-14), and of the Gospel (Luke 21, 25-33) of the first Sun- day of Advent.
